Setup

Add the docker.sh to your bashrc file or bash profile.

Display the $DOCKER_NAME env variable in your PS1 command to display the Docker hostname


Create a ~/.docker/connect folder and create a file for each host exporting Docker environement variable such as:

```
export DOCKER_HOST=docker1:2376
export DOCKER_TLS_VERIFY=1
export DOCKER_CERT_PATH=~/.docker
```
